<i>Are you worried?</i>

22
00:01:26,045 --> 00:01:29,132
PERFORMANCE

23
00:01:30,717 --> 00:01:32,802
Hey, why are we having
more meetings?

24
00:01:32,885 --> 00:01:34,721
I thought we're supposed to meet
every other week?

25
00:01:35,138 --> 00:01:36,514
We have no choice...

26
00:01:36,598 --> 00:01:41,352
Coil reported that Misa Amane
might know L.

27
00:01:42,312 --> 00:01:46,441
According to this,
it means L questioned Amane...

28
00:01:47,025 --> 00:01:48,526
So here's the problem...

29
00:01:49,235 --> 00:01:52,989
He says he's "deduced that
Amane worships Kira."

30
00:01:54,365 --> 00:01:56,242
"Furthermore, Yoshida Productions is

31
00:01:56,326 --> 00:01:59,662
"trying to promote Amane
as the face of Yotsuba."

32
00:01:59,746 --> 00:02:02,206
"I suggest that Yotsuba use Amane
for its commercials. .

33
00:02:02,290 --> 00:02:04,876
"To extract information about L."

34
00:02:06,461 --> 00:02:10,006
I can't accept this idea...

35
00:02:10,798 --> 00:02:13,676
Why not? I think it's a great plan.

36
00:02:14,177 --> 00:02:16,304
No, what Ooi is trying to say is...

37
00:02:16,679 --> 00:02:19,599
It's ultimately Coil's job
to reveal L's identity.

38
00:02:20,183 --> 00:02:23,603
So it's illogical for him
to leave this to us, isn't it?

39
00:02:24,103 --> 00:02:27,940
Yeah. We hired him
to reveal L's identity.

40
00:02:28,608 --> 00:02:31,569
Shouldn't we ask Coil
about his stance?

41
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:33,696
That's true...

42
00:02:35,948 --> 00:02:40,244
Mr. Kida. I thought we'd agreed
you wouldn't contact me directly.

43
00:02:40,745 --> 00:02:41,829
Is it an emergency?

44
00:02:44,666 --> 00:02:45,750
I understand.

45
00:02:46,209 --> 00:02:49,295
If that's the case,
I have a good plan.

46
00:02:51,464 --> 00:02:52,924
Even though the meeting's over,

47
00:02:53,007 --> 00:02:55,051
I still have to punish criminals
when I get home.

48
00:02:55,885 --> 00:02:57,512
It's tough being Kira...

49
00:02:58,471 --> 00:03:00,807
But it's getting interesting...

50
00:03:01,599 --> 00:03:04,769
There's no doubt that Misa Amane
is the Second Kira.

51
00:03:05,019 --> 00:03:06,896
And L caught her at some point.

52
00:03:07,689 --> 00:03:10,108
If he's letting her
move about freely...

53
00:03:10,274 --> 00:03:15,113
It means that she's forfeited ownership
and lost all her memories.

54
00:03:15,947 --> 00:03:18,074
I can't leave her alone.

55
00:03:19,283 --> 00:03:22,370
I'm going to make
Misa Amane my wife.

56
00:03:28,501 --> 00:03:31,754
Money, power, and a beautiful wife...

57
00:03:32,505 --> 00:03:35,007
That's enough to make anyone jealous!

58
00:03:37,885 --> 00:03:39,262
Once we're married...

59
00:03:39,345 --> 00:03:41,597
I'll take out a lot of
life insurance on her...

60
00:03:43,641 --> 00:03:46,436
<i>Impossible. . .he's disgusting.</i>

61
00:03:47,687 --> 00:03:51,274
Rem, hide the notebook
in the usual place.

62
00:04:00,575 --> 00:04:03,369
<i>Right now,
this is the only thing I can do...</i>

63
00:04:04,036 --> 00:04:05,705
<i>for Misa's sake...</i>

64
00:04:08,875 --> 00:04:11,544
All right! Let's take it from there.

65
00:04:11,961 --> 00:04:15,840
Misa, you said that you came
to Tokyo to meet Kira.

66
00:04:16,174 --> 00:04:17,383
- What?!
- Hey!

67
00:04:17,967 --> 00:04:22,054
Misa, please stop overacting.
It looks cheesy.

68
00:04:22,513 --> 00:04:25,057
What? But that's what's called
a realistic performance...

69
00:04:25,516 --> 00:04:26,976
Just do it over...

70
00:04:27,059 --> 00:04:29,562
Yes, yes, oh Great Director Ryuzaki...

71
00:04:29,645 --> 00:04:32,315
If you don't take this seriously,
I'll kick you.

72
00:04:35,902 --> 00:04:37,987
M-Misa-Misa...

73
00:04:38,070 --> 00:04:39,614
You're so tense.

74
00:04:39,697 --> 00:04:41,407
You can just call me "Misa," Mochi.

75
00:04:42,366 --> 00:04:43,826
<i>I'm not suited for this.</i>

76
00:04:44,118 --> 00:04:47,413
<i>But it's still part of
the mission to catch Kira...</i>

77
00:04:47,955 --> 00:04:48,998
Misa-Misa!

78
00:04:49,081 --> 00:04:50,750
What is it, Mochi?!

79
00:04:51,209 --> 00:04:55,379
We're having an interview with Yotsuba
to see if they'll use you in their ads.

80
00:04:55,463 --> 00:04:57,965
But it's also an infiltration.

81
00:04:58,424 --> 00:05:00,468
I know, you don't have to tell me!

82
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:03,721
Of course,
don't blow your cover either, Mochi!

83
00:05:03,805 --> 00:05:07,391
You're supposed to be my energetic
and enthusiastic manager!

84
00:05:07,642 --> 00:05:10,102
Yes, I'll do my best! All right!

85
00:05:11,813 --> 00:05:13,272
Sorry to keep you waiting.

86
00:05:14,023 --> 00:05:15,149
Good morning!

87
00:05:15,566 --> 00:05:19,111
I'm Misa-Misa's manager, Mochi,
also known as Kanichi Moji.

88
00:05:19,195 --> 00:05:20,279
Mr. Ooi,
Mr. Shimura...

89
00:05:20,363 --> 00:05:22,114
- nice to see you again.
- I'm very pleased to meet you.

90
00:05:22,615 --> 00:05:23,866
Good luck, Misa-Misa!

91
00:05:24,367 --> 00:05:26,536
<i>- You 're really na/Y/hg/z', Mach/I</i>
- I'll <i>start planning the party</i>

92
00:05:26,619 --> 00:05:29,288
to celebrate when you
land this commercial!

93
00:05:32,625 --> 00:05:34,961
<i>I'm not cut out for this. . .am I?</i>

94
00:05:38,381 --> 00:05:42,301
Well... This is our first time meeting,
isn't it, Misa?

95
00:05:42,802 --> 00:05:46,138
I'm John Wallace, the executive advisor
for the marketing department.

96
00:05:46,472 --> 00:05:47,640
Pleased to meet you.

97
00:05:47,932 --> 00:05:50,142
Pleased to meet you, too.

98
00:05:50,852 --> 00:05:54,146
This is a bit sudden,
but I'll tell you honestly.

99
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:58,276
We're pretty much certain
we're going to hire you.

100
00:05:58,734 --> 00:06:01,988
But before we do, there's just
one thing we have to clarify.

101
00:06:02,363 --> 00:06:03,406
Yes?

102
00:06:03,489 --> 00:06:05,867
We did a little background
check on you...

103
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:08,828
A burglar killed your parents.

104
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:11,998
You worship the criminal Kira because he
killed the man who murdered your family.

105
00:06:12,206 --> 00:06:16,377
You said that you came to Tokyo
to meet Kira.

106
00:06:18,087 --> 00:06:20,756
Wh-Who did you hear that from?

107
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:22,633
We can't tell you our source.

108
00:06:23,009 --> 00:06:26,053
But this is reliable information.

109
00:06:26,178 --> 00:06:29,223
We can see it written
all over your face.

110
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:33,853
<i>Coil, I never thought
you investigated that far...</i>

111
00:06:34,604 --> 00:06:35,605
Also...

112
00:06:36,022 --> 00:06:38,608
You're still hiding something,
aren't you?

113
00:06:39,233 --> 00:06:41,694
Something that you
don't want anyone to know...

114
00:06:46,699 --> 00:06:50,119
<i>I've g0! f0 sweat a lot
and pause here...</i>

115
00:06:50,912 --> 00:06:53,581
Misa Amane was detained by L...

116
00:06:53,998 --> 00:06:57,335
Please tell us about
what really happened.

117
00:06:57,835 --> 00:07:01,547
It would be a problem
if the face of Yotsuba was Kira.

118
00:07:01,881 --> 00:07:04,383
Yes. Please tell us truthfully.

119
00:07:05,551 --> 00:07:10,264
A-All right.
I'll tell you everything...

120
00:07:11,557 --> 00:07:13,768
I was indeed detained...

121
00:07:14,477 --> 00:07:19,106
I don't think it was L,
but he did ask me about Kira...

122
00:07:19,523 --> 00:07:21,901
But I'm not the Second Kira.

123
00:07:22,443 --> 00:07:26,489
I'm here because he found out
I have nothing to do with Kira.

124
00:07:27,281 --> 00:07:30,034
Did you see
who was detaining you?

125
00:07:30,493 --> 00:07:32,244
I was blindfolded...

126
00:07:33,037 --> 00:07:35,581
But, you heard his voice,
didn't you?

127
00:07:36,082 --> 00:07:38,376
Only through a speaker, so...

128
00:07:38,709 --> 00:07:39,794
Hey...

129
00:07:40,211 --> 00:07:43,547
This is more like an interrogation
rather than an interview.

130
00:07:43,923 --> 00:07:45,216
How long do you plan
on doing this?

131
00:07:45,758 --> 00:07:47,176
I'm going to the restroom.

132
00:07:47,385 --> 00:07:51,097
Indeed, it seems the interview
has veered off track...

133
00:07:54,058 --> 00:07:57,186
Excuse me...
May I also go to the restroom?

134
00:08:00,022 --> 00:08:01,440
<i>This is so stressful!</i>

135
00:08:02,441 --> 00:08:05,444
But it's going well.
I've got to try hard...

136
00:08:13,953 --> 00:08:18,332
<i>Touching her with a piece of the Death Note
won't return her memories...</i>

137
00:08:18,666 --> 00:08:22,503
<i>But at least now,
Misa can see me again...</i>

138
00:08:24,255 --> 00:08:26,549
<i>W-What is this?! A monster?</i>

139
00:08:26,632 --> 00:08:33,556
Misa, you're in a dangerous situation.
The people from Yotsuba may kill you.

140
00:08:34,181 --> 00:08:35,933
I came to tell you that.

141
00:08:36,475 --> 00:08:37,977
Calm down and listen to me.

142
00:08:38,477 --> 00:08:39,895
<i>Calm down?</i>

143
00:08:40,104 --> 00:08:42,732
<i>This monster looks like
it's going to kill me!</i>

144
00:08:43,649 --> 00:08:45,651
I am your ally.

145
00:08:46,152 --> 00:08:49,238
<i>My. . .ally?</i>

146
00:08:50,114 --> 00:08:52,533
I wonder if Misa-Misa is all right...

147
00:08:52,867 --> 00:08:56,203
We should have at least wired her!

148
00:08:57,455 --> 00:08:59,206
<i>It's just as I thought...
They're definitely different people...</i>

149
00:08:59,749 --> 00:09:04,670
<i>The Kira before and after
I was detained. . .are clearly different.</i>

150
00:09:05,337 --> 00:09:06,547
<i>The current Kira is
killing off every criminal...</i>

151
00:09:06,630 --> 00:09:08,758
<i>as soon as they've had
their crime broadcast,</i>

152
00:09:08,841 --> 00:09:10,676
<i>regardless of the situation...</i>

153
00:09:11,218 --> 00:09:14,096
<i>The previous Kira
would never punish...</i>

154
00:09:14,180 --> 00:09:17,099
<i>those who didn't have
any intention to kill,</i>

155
00:09:17,183 --> 00:09:21,979
<i>those who killed by accident, or those
with extenuating circumstances...</i>

156
00:09:23,272 --> 00:09:26,358
<i>If I were Kira,
that's what I would do...</i>

157
00:09:26,859 --> 00:09:29,612
<i>The previous Kira 's
criteria for killing...</i>

158
00:09:29,695 --> 00:09:32,156
<i>are disturbingly close
to my own ideals...</i>

159
00:09:35,868 --> 00:09:37,787
<i>What am I thinking?</i>

160
00:09:38,704 --> 00:09:40,498
<i>I'm not Kira.</i>

161
00:09:40,706 --> 00:09:44,251
<i>I must be crazy to be
comparing myself to Kira...</i>

162
00:09:45,377 --> 00:09:47,046
Light Yagami is Kira.

163
00:09:48,672 --> 00:09:51,175
What is Light doing now?

164
00:10:00,392 --> 00:10:01,727
What are you?

165
00:10:02,436 --> 00:10:06,857
I know you're not a stalker,
but you don't look human at all...

166
00:10:07,274 --> 00:10:10,861
Of course. I'm a Shinigami.

167
00:10:12,196 --> 00:10:15,783
Misa, we once worked together.

168
00:10:16,283 --> 00:10:18,577
I don't know what
you're talking about...

169
00:10:19,036 --> 00:10:21,747
You met me? Light is Kira?

170
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:24,416
The Death Note...

171
00:10:26,252 --> 00:10:32,550
If you write a person's name in it,
that person dies...

172
00:10:33,759 --> 00:10:35,052
With that notebook,

173
00:10:35,136 --> 00:10:40,432
Light Yagami punished criminals
and became known as Kira.

174
00:10:43,936 --> 00:10:49,567
And you had the same...no,
greater power than Kira.

175
00:10:50,693 --> 00:10:55,948
With that power you succeeded in
getting close to Light Yagami.

176
00:10:56,657 --> 00:11:00,202
Light is Kira...
and I'm the Second Kira?

177
00:11:00,619 --> 00:11:03,831
That's right...
No, more correctly, you were.

178
00:11:04,623 --> 00:11:09,211
This should all be going
according to Light's plan.

179
00:11:10,296 --> 00:11:12,715
<i>So Ryuzaki's right!</i>

180
00:11:14,175 --> 00:11:17,970
Misa... Do you still love Light
more than anything?

181
00:11:21,390 --> 00:11:24,476
Shinigami, you really are
the real thing.

182
00:11:24,810 --> 00:11:27,021
You know everything about me.

183
00:11:27,479 --> 00:11:29,481
I'll believe everything you say...

184
00:11:30,566 --> 00:11:33,861
Yes... I love him...more than anything.

185
00:11:34,570 --> 00:11:41,327
Besides, it's really awesome
that Light and I were both Kira.

186
00:11:41,744 --> 00:11:42,786
I believe you!

187
00:11:43,454 --> 00:11:45,831
You haven't changed at all, Misa...

188
00:11:46,373 --> 00:11:50,085
Those feelings towards Light will
probably never change, will they?

189
00:11:50,586 --> 00:11:57,343
I now believe that you'll find
happiness by staying with Light.

190
00:11:57,843 --> 00:11:59,678
Thank you, Shinigami.

191
00:12:00,179 --> 00:12:01,180
It's Rem.

192
00:12:01,430 --> 00:12:04,350
The current Kira is a crooked
and pathetic human.

193
00:12:04,892 --> 00:12:08,354
You don't know what he'll do.
Be careful.

194
00:12:08,687 --> 00:12:10,689
Be careful of
the other Yotsuba men, as well.

195
00:12:11,190 --> 00:12:14,235
<i>Trust Light and let him do
whatever he feels necessary.</i>

196
00:12:15,069 --> 00:12:19,031
<i>All right, I just have to
act normal, right?</i>

197
00:12:19,365 --> 00:12:20,366
<i>That's right.</i>

198
00:12:20,824 --> 00:12:23,077
<i>When you go back to the interview,</i>

199
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:28,290
<i>you should be able to tell who's Kira.
Do not trust him...</i>

200
00:12:29,708 --> 00:12:32,211
Sorry I took so long in the restroom.

201
00:12:32,628 --> 00:12:34,755
I fixed up my makeup.

202
00:12:36,423 --> 00:12:42,554
<i>All right, when you return, the man
who's sitting in front of me is Kira.</i>

203
00:12:42,930 --> 00:12:43,931
<i>Rem...</i>

204
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:46,517
<i>The person in front of Rem is Kira...</i>

205
00:12:56,443 --> 00:12:57,987
<i>Higuchi is Kira.</i>

206
00:12:58,696 --> 00:12:59,863
<i>That's horrible...</i>

207
00:13:10,833 --> 00:13:13,127
Misa-Misa sure is late...

208
00:13:16,088 --> 00:13:17,381
They're back!

209
00:13:17,548 --> 00:13:18,549
Hey!

210
00:13:19,925 --> 00:13:22,219
I am so tired.

211
00:13:22,636 --> 00:13:23,637
Hey...

212
00:13:23,721 --> 00:13:24,763
How was it?

213
00:13:25,055 --> 00:13:29,018
Yotsuba has hired Misa
to appear in their ads.

214
00:13:29,685 --> 00:13:31,895
I see. That's great.

215
00:13:32,354 --> 00:13:34,732
Once I told them
my cell phone number,

216
00:13:34,898 --> 00:13:39,361
I got asked out
by three of the seven already.

217
00:13:39,528 --> 00:13:40,612
What?

218
00:13:40,863 --> 00:13:43,741
I just have to accept
and investigate them, right?

219
00:13:43,907 --> 00:13:45,326
It's going exactly as planned.

220
00:13:45,492 --> 00:13:47,453
No, the plan has been cancelled.

221
00:13:48,245 --> 00:13:51,415
Why? It's been going so well...

222
00:13:51,707 --> 00:13:53,876
You'll be in danger if we do this.

223
00:13:54,710 --> 00:13:56,962
I won't stop you from appearing
in any of their commercials,

224
00:13:57,046 --> 00:14:00,049
but from now on, deny that you were
suspected of being the Second Kira

225
00:14:00,132 --> 00:14:02,009
and that you were
detained by L.

226
00:14:02,593 --> 00:14:04,762
Mogi will be your bodyguard...

227
00:14:05,095 --> 00:14:06,847
and you will just be
an entertainer.

228
00:14:10,225 --> 00:14:13,479
If that's what you say,
then that's what I'll do...

229
00:14:16,106 --> 00:14:19,068
Well, I'm tired and tomorrow's shoot
is early in the morning,

230
00:14:19,151 --> 00:14:20,235
so I'm going to bed.

231
00:14:22,696 --> 00:14:25,783
<i>Thank you for worrying
about me, Light...</i>

232
00:14:26,283 --> 00:14:28,744
<i>But I've come up with a good plan!</i>

233
00:14:29,870 --> 00:14:31,830
<i>I'm gonna be of use to you!</i>

